 *********** KAFKA Architecture and Components ********
  
  
  => Event
  => Producer
  => Consumer
  => Topics
  => Partitions
  => Consumer Groups
  => Offset
  => Consumer Rebalancing
  
  
  => Events(Something Happened + Its Data)
  
  	- Any meaningful action is called event
  	- e.g.  Order placed ,Restaurant Accepted order, Payment done 
    - Event is not just message that this event is happened but it also has its data
    - like Order placed will have data like Order id, payment id, order amt ...etc
  
   => Producer(Producer is nothing but sender)
   
   		- Producer is someone who produces the event
   		- In Kafka any service that produces an event is producer
   		- Order service creates event order placed so order service is producer, there can be N number of producers
   	
   => Consumer
   
   	- Consumer is someone who is consuming that particular event
   	- suppose Order service created event Order Placed -> Notification service will be consumer, restaurant service will be consumer, Invoice service will consumer
   
   => Topics
   
   	- Its like channel for receiving messages/events
   	- way of segregating messages within kafka
   	- Because if we have 10 producers liek Order service, Customer service, Paymetn service etc all messages go in kafka if there is no segregation its chaos
   	- Its best to have some sort of segregation so there is no chaos, that will be easy for consumers to consume data
   	- Because we have consumer , so consumer will say i'm notification service i just want to read the order related messages, so what we can do is
   	 we can have a topic called order  and the producer i.e. order service  can send the order related or order confirmation data to that particular topic
   	- then notification service can just listen to that topic , It does not care about other topic
   	- So Topic is like named group or channel for messages
   	- Its segregation in kafka
   	
   => Partitions
   	- Within topic there might be  lots of msgs, lates say sale day, In the Topics there is concept of partition like partition1, partition2 they will do further segregation within topic itself
   	- e.g. lets say we have topic Order -> we can have sub partition so that different consumers can subscribe or listen to those partitions and do the processing
   	
    => Consumer Groups
    
    - If we have partitions we will need team of consumers also for sharing message load 
    - if 1 million order placed then 1 million events will be sent to order topic in different partitions
    - so we should have a team of consumers consuming messages/events quickly, so in that case we can have consumers that are grouped together, we can name that group as well
    - So this is  basically a team of consumers sharing a message load for that particular topic and they are listenening to individual partitions
   
   => Consumer Rebalancing
   
   	-  It's a process of redistributing the topic partition among the consumer within the consumer group, which ensures that consumer is assigned a fair share of partition to read and process
   	- It happens automatically when consumer joins or leaves or changes within the group or when new partitions are added
   	
   => Offset
   
   	- In one line we can say it's like bookmark of your last read message
   	- In whatsapp it shows from where messages are unread,  unread messages
   	- In kafka offset is number showing position of last message read
  
  - There are multiple instances of kafka running, those instances are call broker inside Cluster
  - Suppose we have four kafka instances running together all  these instances can run in cluster because they are serving the same application
  - Why we need to have multiple instances of kafka ?
  	for better load management, if there is lot of load
  - If lot of things are running in cluster 
  	we will need some sort of manager who will keep track or who will coordinate all the brokers in a cluster, that is where zookeeper comes in picture
  - Zookeeper is a service that helps to manage the entire kafka cluster 
  - in newer version of kafka , kafka is moving away feom zookeeper
  - because when we install kafka, we will need to install kafka first, for less dependency
