  ==> Functional Interface
  
  	- A functional interface in java is an interface that contains exactly one abstract method
  	- @Functional Interface
  	-Built in Functional Interface
  	
  	-> Function<T,R>
  	
  		- Function takes input of Type T, returns something of type R
  		- e.g. Function<String,Integer> getLength= s->s.length();
  			sysout(getLength.apply("Sushant"))
  			
  		
  			
  	- Consumer<T>
  	
  		- Takes input of type T , does something, but returns nothing
  		
  		Consumer<String> printer=s-> Sysout("Message : "+s);
  		printer.accept("Hello-World");
  		
  		
  	- Supplier<T>
  	
  		- Takes no input, returns a value of type T
  		
  		Supplier<String> giveMessage=()->"Hello from supplier";
  		Sysout(giveMessage.get());
  		
  	- Predicate<T>
  	
  		- Takes the input, returns true or false
  		
  		e.g. Predicate<String> isLong=s->s.length()>5;
  		
  			Sysout(isLong.test("Hello"));
